content.visibleText:
Jigsaw
Slot #1
Progress week 22b
Rollout plan
No changes on the conversion funnel
Outreach to high ARR Customers as Messenger & Monitor Releases become available
Follow-up after customers open support tickets for new releases to understand their upgrade path and user requirements and help them remove blockers for upgrading (if any)
Keep track of releases deployed in the test environment (or production)
Rollout MIPs
1) Getting requirements and success criteria for SoftwareAG ($0.9M)
2) Establish lease with licenses to the BU team/customer; Customer can not proceed without the signed documentation
3) Clarify to SA that this issue may/will cause large delays, and we need clear requirements & tests cases.
4) Lufthansa base version is 2022 and the fix we provided is on top of 2023. Consequently, they are asking for a fix on their current version. while the fix struggling with upgrade as it is not made for their 2022 deployed version
Plan Week 23*
1) Complete Phone Call Attempts Outreach to Customers
2) Support Lufthansa for upgrading software.
3) Monitor and keep pushing SoftwareAG to set up Webmethods environment.
Insights from customers
Broadridge - the initial inquiry came from the Application team but the Infrastructure team has no plans to upgrade as they still have issues with version 'Still have issues with 1.2.0,' which they upgraded to upgrade in 2022. They push for a new low from Application department to currently upgrading to 1.2.0.3
Proximity (S1M) - currently upgrading products over 2 years version; No plans for 14 upgrade. Refineries: upgrades are planned 9 months to 1-3 year in advance; We missed the current cycle. They still have problems upgrading to version 12.0
See individual customer summaries
